   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s last known letter to Warren was of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0229" class="document">9 Dec. 1780</a> (vol. 10:404).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d094n2-ptr" id="PJA13d094n2">2</a>

   <p>For Mercy Otis Warrens response, see her letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0255" class="document">25 Oct.</a>, below.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d094n3-ptr" id="PJA13d094n3">3</a>

   <p>A reference to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Abigail Adams (17441818), m. John Adams 1764 ]">AA</abbr>s plan to purchase land in Vermont as a retreat for <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, for which see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Adams Family Correspondence&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. H. Butterfield, Marc Friedlaender, Richard Alan Ryerson, Margaret A. Hogan, and others, Cambridge, 1963?. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">AFC</span></span>, 4:<a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-04-02-0174" class="document">257258</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-04-02-0195" class="document">293</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-04-02-0209" class="document">315317</a>.</p>

